      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;installing-conda-package-on-macos&#34;&gt;Installing Conda package on macOS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;brew install --cask conda
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This will download &lt;code&gt;miniconda&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;coda&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;anaconda3&lt;/code&gt; and all other required affiliated packages. The install location may vary, but is most likely to be in &lt;code&gt;/usr/local/anaconda3/&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After the installation, add the path to the &lt;code&gt;anaconda3&lt;/code&gt; installation directory to the &lt;code&gt;$PATH&lt;/code&gt; system variable, by:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s1&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;export PATH=&amp;#34;/usr/local/anaconda3/bin:$PATH&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; ~/.zshrc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;source&lt;/span&gt; ~/.zshrc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;initializing-conda-environment&#34;&gt;Initializing Conda Environment&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Initialize &lt;code&gt;conda&lt;/code&gt; for your shell permanently:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;conda init
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This will add command lines to your &lt;code&gt;~/.zshrc&lt;/code&gt; file to initialize conda path variables at each startup. The modified &lt;code&gt;~/.zshrc&lt;/code&gt; file looks like:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
